doc.after: Croatian traditional cuisine varies from one region to another Dalmatia and Istria draw upon culinary influences of Italian and other Mediterranean cuisines which prominently feature various seafood cooked vegetables and pasta as well as condiments such as olive oil and garlic The continental cuisine is heavily influenced by Hungarian Austrian and Turkish culinary styles In that area meats freshwater fish and vegetable dishes are predominant 241
